# Helsinki Weathere 🌦️

A full-stack web app that pulls live weather data for Helsinki, stores it locally over time, and visualizes temperature and wind speed trends through a dashboard built in React — backend in FastAPI, database in SQLite.

## What it does

- Fetches real weather data from [Open-Meteo](https://open-meteo.com/) every hour automatically
- Stores historical readings in a local SQLite database
- Serves the data through a FastAPI REST API
- Displays live charts and current conditions in a React dashboard

## Stack

- **Frontend** — React, Recharts, Tailwind CSS
- **Backend** — Python, FastAPI
- **Database** — SQLite
- **Data** — Open-Meteo API (Helsinki, Finland)

## Running locally

Make sure you have Python and Node.js installed, then:

```bash
# Install Python dependencies
pip install fastapi uvicorn requests

# Install frontend dependencies
cd frontend && npm install && cd ..

# Run everything
python run.py
```

Open `http://localhost:5173` in your browser.

## Project structure

```
weathere/
├── frontend/        # React app
├── backend/
│   ├── main.py      # FastAPI routes
│   ├── database.py  # SQLite connection
│   ├── fetcher.py   # Hourly data collection
│   └── data/
│       └── db.sqlite
└── run.py           # Starts both servers
```

